review_blob: From bottle, 33cl. Weak slightly hay-like aroma, with a hazy pale amber colour. Indistinct flavour.

Bought from Tesco, 33cl bottle. Tastes a roasty, caramel flavour. Amber with a clear, minimal head. Of a  medium sweetness, lightly bitter, lightly sour.  Light on the palate with a slick and thin feel
Drank from bottle, 33cl. Pours a cloudy, orange/crimson colour, with a deep fruity aroma. Smooth on the palate, with a tangy and rich flavour
On tap at The Head of Steam, Durham. Beautifully distinct, slightly caramel-esque aroma. Hazy straw-coloured appearance . An extremely complex and involving taste (I wish I could dissect it!).
Pint can, served in the proper glass. Mild aroma, but decent for a common lager, with a clear amber colour. A mild taste with a hint of distinction; not particularly interesting on the palate.

Drank from bottle, 33cl. Strong and powerful IPA aroma, with a cloudy orange colour. Bitter on the palate, with a pleasant and mild sting, and an overpowering (slightly too overpowering) flavour and a distinctive after taste.
